<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/62358230-leon-stephens"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/62358230-leon-stephens">Leon Stephens</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The most important thing to know is that all translations are bad in comparison with the original, so the best thing is to study Italian. Failing that<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The most important thing to know is that all translations are bad in comparison with the original, so the best thing is to study Italian. Failing that, I would recommend mine as the least bad. It's bilingual, in three volumes, available at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.lulu.com/spotlight/pluramon">www.lulu.com/spotlight/pluramon</a>. It took me 36 years to complete it. To read a sample, click on the title and then on the word Preview under the enlarged cover photo that will then appear. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
