        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer169579533" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11796966818567101812">I am so glad for the Divine Comedy and Decameron group for providing the structure and encouragement which provided the impetus for my finally reading this classic! I am also very pleased that I decided to read John Ciardi&apos;s translation as his synopsis and notes added immeasurably to my reading. <br/><br/>While personally I found Dante&apos;s travel&apos;s through Hell occasionally difficult, the Purgatorio and Paradiso (except for the first few scholarly cantos) flowed with beautiful poetry. And through it all, Da</span>
  <span id="freeText11796966818567101812" style="display:none">I am so glad for the Divine Comedy and Decameron group for providing the structure and encouragement which provided the impetus for my finally reading this classic! I am also very pleased that I decided to read John Ciardi's translation as his synopsis and notes added immeasurably to my reading. <br /><br />While personally I found Dante's travel's through Hell occasionally difficult, the Purgatorio and Paradiso (except for the first few scholarly cantos) flowed with beautiful poetry. And through it all, Dante maintained his amazing, and consistent, vision.<br /><br />No wonder this has stood the test of time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11796966818567101812" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
